PGD
Computes gradient of loss w.r.t. image.
Updates image in gradient direction.
Simplest iterative attack.
MI-FGSM
Adds momentum accumulation.
Prevents unstable gradient directions.
Improves transferability.
TI-FGSM
Applies Gaussian smoothing to gradients.
Makes perturbations less location-specific.
Improves black-box transfer.
SI-NI-FGSM
Computes gradients at multiple image scales.
Uses Nesterov momentum.
Produces more generalized perturbations.
MI-ADMIX-DI-TI
Mixes images (ADMIX).
Uses random resizing/padding (DI).
Uses momentum (MI).
Uses gradient smoothing (TI).
Strongest baseline in repository.
